The paper proposes a novel neural network architecture for power demand forecasting, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the optimization of operational cost for generation and transmission, which relates to control systems (cs.SY). The use of historical energy consumption data, weather data, and calendar information suggests the use of data science techniques (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses anomaly detection, which is a common topic in neural networks and machine learning (cs.NE).
